I'm actually redrawing these scenes to help me cope.  I get to recreate art I made when I was really depressed in college/post college. 

And seeing it at the quality and standards I have for my art now? It feels amazing.

I don't say it enough... 

So I want to say: Thank you.  

Thank you for supporting me and my art. Thank you for telling me that you actually enjoy what I make.  Space Dandy is one of the few things that can make me happy in life.  Anxiety and Stress makes enjoying life difficult

Hearing that people actually like my comics or my art does genuinely make my day.  Hearing "that comic where Dandy smacks the rock's ass still makes laugh" or "QT saying "I love Phil collins, you have seduced me, Dandy" cracks me up" really makes me happy ;;

I need to remember that I draw that space dandy art for myself. 99% of the tweets are flops.   It doesn't matter if I spend five seconds or 3 days on it.  I feel like no one can see it.

And with all this shit going on: I have to ignore numbers. It only depresses me.

Going to keep the depressed tweeting to a minimum but damn.
